  "response_text": "### The Echoes of Time\n\nIn the small village of Eldoria, nestled between whispering woods and towering mountains, there lived an old clockmaker named Eli. Eli was known for his intricate timepieces, each one more complex than the last. His latest creation, however, was unlike any other. It was a clock that could tell the time not just in hours and minutes, but also in stories.\n\nEli\u2019s clock had a unique feature: it could tell a story about itself every hour. But here\u2019s the twist\u2014each story it told was a reflection of the previous one, creating a loop of narratives that seemed to go on forever. The villagers were fascinated by this clock, but they never understood why Eli kept adding more layers to its storytelling mechanism.\n\nOne day, a curious young boy named Timmy asked Eli, \u201cWhy do you keep making your clock tell more and more stories? It seems like it will never end.\u201d\n\nEli smiled and said, \u201cTimmy, my",
